WEBVTT

00:02.393 --> 00:04.874
[Connie Conway's
"Too Lovely To Forget"]

00:04.917 --> 00:07.790
[thunder booming]

00:07.833 --> 00:10.749
[wind whooshing]

00:11.924 --> 00:15.667
- ♪ A love I thought
would last ♪

00:15.711 --> 00:19.323
♪ For a life time

00:19.367 --> 00:25.242
♪ Has ended
in tears of regret ♪

00:25.286 --> 00:31.292
♪ And now I'm alone
with just memories of you ♪

00:31.335 --> 00:36.123
♪ Too lovely to forget

00:36.166 --> 00:38.299
♪ I dream of you

00:38.342 --> 00:43.086
♪ Through each long
dreary night time ♪

00:43.130 --> 00:45.349
♪ 'Cause dreaming
is all I have left ♪

00:45.393 --> 00:48.048
[thunder booms]

00:48.091 --> 00:53.270
- I wish I never brought you
back from that damn island.

00:53.314 --> 00:55.446
- How strange.

00:55.490 --> 00:57.274
You never cursed me
while I was helping you

00:57.318 --> 00:59.450
find fame and fortunate.

00:59.494 --> 01:03.106
- You ruined the lives
of my colleagues and friends.

01:03.150 --> 01:05.369
- Did I?
[chuckles]

01:05.413 --> 01:09.025
Those pretty much sound
like your choices.

01:09.069 --> 01:12.202
Too late to grow a conscience
now, don't you think?

01:12.246 --> 01:14.335
- I don't want this anymore.

01:14.378 --> 01:19.035
- But we have
so much more to do.

01:19.079 --> 01:21.342
You owe me.

01:21.385 --> 01:24.997
- You leave me alone!
[glass shatters]

01:27.087 --> 01:31.091
- Bruce, if you really want me
to leave you alone,

01:31.134 --> 01:35.225
put the diamond down.

01:35.269 --> 01:38.141
You can't, can you?

01:38.185 --> 01:41.144
Because you can't let go
of power.

01:41.188 --> 01:45.366
[chuckles]

01:45.409 --> 01:50.327
♪

01:50.371 --> 01:52.460
[gun clicks]

02:01.208 --> 02:04.254
What if I could fix it all?

02:04.298 --> 02:06.126
- Fix it?

02:06.169 --> 02:07.649
You've broken everything.

02:07.692 --> 02:11.566
- I feel you, Bruce.
I feel your loneliness.

02:11.609 --> 02:14.177
But you're not alone.

02:14.221 --> 02:18.312
I am here for you.

02:18.355 --> 02:20.401
You lost her once.

02:20.444 --> 02:23.273
You let her go.

02:23.317 --> 02:25.971
[ominous music]

02:26.015 --> 02:29.279
We can get her back.

02:29.323 --> 02:32.543
- Mona?
- Yes.

02:32.587 --> 02:34.545
Her husband's the only thing

02:34.589 --> 02:37.069
that stands
between you and her.

02:37.113 --> 02:38.636
Nothing else.

02:38.680 --> 02:40.682
- You don't know her.

02:40.725 --> 02:46.383
- I know once he's gone,
Mona will be all yours.

02:46.427 --> 02:50.518
Her heart, her body,

02:50.561 --> 02:53.216
and her soul--

02:53.260 --> 02:56.219
she'll be yours
despite your fraud self.

02:56.263 --> 02:58.395
Forever.

02:58.439 --> 03:03.095
♪

03:03.139 --> 03:05.707
- I won't kill anyone.

03:05.750 --> 03:09.885
- [chuckles]
Not you, Bruce.

03:09.928 --> 03:11.234
Me.

03:11.278 --> 03:13.715
I'll do it.

03:13.758 --> 03:18.676
Let me take control and
you'll never be alone again.

03:18.720 --> 03:22.550
All you have to do
is drop the gun

03:22.593 --> 03:25.074
and watch me do it.

03:25.117 --> 03:29.774
♪

03:29.818 --> 03:35.258
Drop the gun.
Let me take control.

03:35.302 --> 03:38.827
That's all you have to do.

03:38.870 --> 03:41.525
After all I've done for you,

03:41.569 --> 03:46.443
you owe me.

03:46.487 --> 03:49.054
♪

03:49.098 --> 03:52.057
- [screams]

03:52.101 --> 03:54.886
[dramatic music]

03:54.930 --> 04:01.980
♪

04:08.378 --> 04:12.339
[soft dramatic music]

04:12.382 --> 04:15.429
[thunder rumbling]

04:19.737 --> 04:21.478
- They're sending us all home.

04:21.522 --> 04:24.176
- Why?
- Storm's rolling in.

04:24.220 --> 04:26.222
We haven't got much time.

04:26.266 --> 04:27.397
Hey, be careful out there.

04:27.441 --> 04:30.487
- Okay, yeah, you too.
- Okay.

04:37.929 --> 04:44.980
♪

04:53.510 --> 04:56.252
- Okay.
Yes, sir.

04:59.299 --> 05:00.865
- Okay, Mike,
so we're not gonna be down

05:00.909 --> 05:03.346
in the basement for a month,
all right?

05:03.390 --> 05:05.348
- Didn't you say we should
prepare for the worst?

05:05.392 --> 05:09.352
- I did, so go get the sleeping
bags, upstairs closet, please.

05:09.396 --> 05:11.006
Thank you.

05:12.747 --> 05:16.359
- Watch out.
He's in a mood.

05:16.403 --> 05:19.362
- Rick's hearing was canceled.

05:19.406 --> 05:21.451
- That's okay.
He'll be safe in jail.

05:21.495 --> 05:23.888
- Nowhere's safe, Pat.

05:23.932 --> 05:26.761
And we can't just let Rick rot
in a cell.

05:26.804 --> 05:28.502
- Right, we're gonna see
what we can do

05:28.545 --> 05:30.808
after the storm clears.

05:30.852 --> 05:34.377
- This storm isn't passing,
and you know that.

05:34.421 --> 05:38.729
And we all know
who's causing it.

05:38.773 --> 05:44.300
After what he did to Yolanda
and Rick and Beth--

05:44.344 --> 05:46.824
she saw him, Pat,

05:46.868 --> 05:50.480
in what she thought
was our house.

05:50.524 --> 05:54.615
He's getting stronger.
[sighs]

05:54.658 --> 05:59.271
So Beth and I decided we're
not waiting around anymore.

05:59.315 --> 06:01.796
- Okay, well, I'm sorry,
but what does that mean?

06:01.839 --> 06:03.711
- It means as soon
as we find Eclipso,

06:03.754 --> 06:05.365
we have to go after him

06:05.408 --> 06:08.585
with whoever
and whatever we have left.

06:08.629 --> 06:10.500
- Court, just please do me--

06:10.544 --> 06:12.502
- And since you don't know how
the JSA stopped him last time,

06:12.546 --> 06:14.504
we're gonna have
to figure it out ourselves.

06:14.548 --> 06:16.593
- We are not prepared.

06:16.637 --> 06:18.943
- Pat, I love you,

06:18.987 --> 06:22.643
but when have we ever
been prepared enough

06:22.686 --> 06:24.993
to make you happy?

06:27.474 --> 06:29.084
I'm gonna go call Beth.

06:29.127 --> 06:31.565
I'll let you know as soon
as we find the center

06:31.608 --> 06:34.568
of this storm.

06:34.611 --> 06:37.571
[soft music]

06:37.614 --> 06:44.665
♪

07:02.509 --> 07:04.336
[woman sobs]

07:07.514 --> 07:13.041
- We are gathered here today
to lay to rest Rebecca McNider,

07:13.084 --> 07:16.044
gone too soon.

07:16.087 --> 07:18.655
The Lord bless you
and watch over you.

07:18.699 --> 07:20.614
Lord make his face shine
upon you

07:20.657 --> 07:23.094
and be gracious to you.

07:23.138 --> 07:27.229
Lord look kindly on you
and give you peace.

07:27.272 --> 07:30.624
In the name of the Father,
and of the Son,

07:30.667 --> 07:33.888
and of the Holy Spirit, amen.

07:33.931 --> 07:36.456
- Amen.
- Amen.

07:36.499 --> 07:38.501
♪

07:38.545 --> 07:41.678
[device beeping]

07:45.726 --> 07:48.250
- You know if the Thunderbolt
could help, I would ask.

07:48.293 --> 07:51.340
Nobody can bring Rebecca back,
Johnny.

07:51.383 --> 07:55.257
♪

07:55.300 --> 07:57.520
- How could someone do that
to a child?

07:57.564 --> 08:00.218
- Not someone, Sly.
Something.

08:00.262 --> 08:01.916
- What's it want?
- Whatever it is,

08:01.959 --> 08:03.395
we have to stop it.

08:03.439 --> 08:07.443
- We will, Rex.
We'll catch that monster.

08:07.487 --> 08:08.923
- Flash.

08:08.966 --> 08:11.534
- Pat, we're in public.

08:11.578 --> 08:14.885
- Right, sorry.
Jay, Jay.

08:14.929 --> 08:17.758
- Hello, Stripesy.
- Hi.

08:17.801 --> 08:19.934
- We know
that it's called Eclipso.

08:19.977 --> 08:21.544
- Where does it come from?

08:21.588 --> 08:25.983
- Pat, let the members
ask the questions.

08:26.027 --> 08:28.769
- Right.
- It comes from an island.

08:28.812 --> 08:30.858
We believe it was
brought back here

08:30.901 --> 08:34.470
by an explorer
named Bruce Gordon.

08:34.514 --> 08:35.950
- This is your fault, Charles!

08:35.993 --> 08:39.214
- Myra, please.
- No, you weren't there!

08:39.257 --> 08:43.566
You didn't see what it did
to our little girl!

08:43.610 --> 08:45.133
- Myra.

08:45.176 --> 08:49.267
- [sobbing]
- Myra.

08:49.311 --> 08:56.361
♪

09:17.644 --> 09:20.603
[child giggling]

09:20.647 --> 09:25.652
[tense music]

09:25.695 --> 09:28.655
[indistinct whispers]

09:28.698 --> 09:35.749
♪

09:57.727 --> 10:00.817
[lid creaking]

10:07.519 --> 10:10.348
- Liar, liar.
You are a liar.

10:10.392 --> 10:12.133
- But, Mom,
I got my flower dress on.

10:12.176 --> 10:16.354
- She's gonna find out.
You know she will.

10:16.398 --> 10:23.448
♪

10:24.014 --> 10:26.756
[child laughing]

10:26.800 --> 10:29.890
Liar!

10:29.933 --> 10:36.984
♪

10:49.649 --> 10:51.912
- So let's go over
what we know.

10:51.955 --> 10:54.523
We know your goggles can see
through his illusions.

10:54.566 --> 10:56.351
That's one advantage we have
over him.

10:56.394 --> 10:59.746
[indistinct speech over phone]

10:59.789 --> 11:01.008
Good.

11:01.051 --> 11:05.665
We also know
the Staff hurt Eclipso before.

11:05.708 --> 11:07.275
The Staff may still be weak,

11:07.318 --> 11:10.017
but if we can use it
with your goggles somehow,

11:10.060 --> 11:12.976
maybe there's something
we can do.

11:13.020 --> 11:16.676
[indistinct speech over phone]

11:16.719 --> 11:20.636
Yolanda hasn't
called me back either.

11:28.992 --> 11:32.692
- Dad.

11:32.735 --> 11:34.868
Dad.

11:34.911 --> 11:37.871
[foreboding music]

11:37.914 --> 11:40.569
♪

11:40.612 --> 11:43.311
Dad?

11:43.354 --> 11:50.666
♪

11:52.712 --> 11:55.715
Is the heat out or something?

11:55.758 --> 11:58.456
[wind whooshing]

11:58.500 --> 12:05.768
♪

12:07.857 --> 12:10.381
Dad?

12:15.430 --> 12:18.389
[soft somber music]

12:18.433 --> 12:25.745
♪

12:55.426 --> 12:58.255
- What do we do now?

12:58.299 --> 12:59.953
- We're gonna find
this Bruce Gordon

12:59.996 --> 13:01.868
and see what he knows.

13:01.911 --> 13:05.001
- Dr. McNider was my friend,
too, Sylvester.

13:05.045 --> 13:07.874
And, you know, I want to be
a part of getting justice

13:07.917 --> 13:09.353
for his daughter.

13:09.397 --> 13:12.269
Look, I know
I'm not on the team.

13:12.313 --> 13:14.837
But please, Sylvester,
this is different.

13:14.881 --> 13:16.752
- I know it is.

13:16.796 --> 13:19.842
God, Pat.
She was only ten.

13:22.149 --> 13:25.979
We can't let this happen again.

13:26.022 --> 13:28.851
♪

13:28.895 --> 13:31.854
- Is that...
- The Shade.

13:31.898 --> 13:32.986
- I'll get the others.
- No.

13:33.029 --> 13:34.683
If The Shade wanted to fight,

13:34.726 --> 13:37.773
he wouldn't be staring us down
in broad daylight.

13:37.817 --> 13:39.383
I'll meet you back
at the garage.

13:39.427 --> 13:40.645
- But, Sylvester,
I thought that--

13:40.689 --> 13:43.126
- Go, and we'll talk later

13:43.170 --> 13:46.042
about getting you
more involved.

13:46.086 --> 13:49.089
- Okay.

13:49.132 --> 13:55.922
♪

14:20.860 --> 14:22.426
- Thank you, Brady Bob.

14:22.470 --> 14:24.951
I'm here just off
of Main Street in downtown.

14:24.994 --> 14:27.257
And as you can see
behind me, the--

14:27.301 --> 14:28.868
[radio static]

14:28.911 --> 14:30.913
Upwards of 40 miles an hour.

14:30.957 --> 14:32.959
All the--
[radio static]

14:33.002 --> 14:34.743
Closed.

14:34.786 --> 14:36.788
[radio static]
Gone home.

14:36.832 --> 14:39.052
[radio static]
Completely--

14:39.095 --> 14:40.749
[radio static]

14:40.792 --> 14:43.534
[engine sputters, shuts off]

14:43.578 --> 14:47.625
♪

14:47.669 --> 14:50.977
[engine grinding]

14:54.545 --> 14:58.158
[tense music]

14:58.201 --> 15:00.987
[thunder rumbling]

15:02.684 --> 15:09.169
♪

15:13.825 --> 15:17.003
[soft dramatic music]

15:17.046 --> 15:24.097
♪

15:47.816 --> 15:50.993
[mellow pop music]

15:51.037 --> 15:56.825
♪

15:56.868 --> 16:01.221
- ♪ When the day is done

16:01.264 --> 16:06.878
♪ And you're all alone

16:06.922 --> 16:10.839
♪ And your heart
has been broken ♪

16:10.882 --> 16:13.711
♪ And torn

16:13.755 --> 16:17.106
♪ That's when
I will run to you ♪

16:17.150 --> 16:22.372
♪ And stay till the hurt
is all gone ♪

16:22.416 --> 16:24.592
[elevator dings]

16:24.635 --> 16:27.464
♪ When the clouds are gray

16:27.508 --> 16:31.381
♪

16:31.425 --> 16:35.516
- What happened?

16:35.559 --> 16:37.170
Sylvester?

16:37.213 --> 16:40.042
- Pat, Pat, uh,

16:40.086 --> 16:44.133
what we're facing,
it's not...

16:44.177 --> 16:46.701
human.

16:46.744 --> 16:48.920
- What is it?

16:48.964 --> 16:52.489
- The Shade called it a...

16:52.533 --> 16:55.623
spiritual parasite.

16:55.666 --> 16:58.887
Like an otherworldly creature.

16:58.930 --> 17:03.196
Somehow,
this Bruce Gordon found it.

17:03.239 --> 17:05.154
And now it's possessed him.

17:05.198 --> 17:07.330
I mean, this thing
can make you see it

17:07.374 --> 17:09.767
as anything it wants.

17:09.811 --> 17:15.512
It can make
your nightmares come true.

17:15.556 --> 17:18.820
And he told me
how we can stop it.

17:18.863 --> 17:23.390
- But why would The Shade
help us?

17:23.433 --> 17:27.089
- I saw fear in his eyes

17:27.133 --> 17:31.354
when he told me
that he had faced it before.

17:31.398 --> 17:33.574
I mean, this thing--

17:33.617 --> 17:38.100
it murdered men, women,

17:38.144 --> 17:41.408
children.

17:41.451 --> 17:45.281
I mean, he called it...

17:45.325 --> 17:47.718
real evil.

17:47.762 --> 17:51.244
[foreboding music]

17:51.287 --> 17:56.640
He said the only way to stop it
is to kill the host.

17:59.730 --> 18:02.298
- Kill the host?

18:06.737 --> 18:10.176
You're talking about
killing another human?

18:10.219 --> 18:13.701
- When the host dies,

18:13.744 --> 18:18.053
Eclipso will be forced back
into the diamond.

18:18.097 --> 18:19.968
And as long
as we don't touch it,

18:20.011 --> 18:22.666
as long as no one does,

18:22.710 --> 18:24.451
Eclipso will
be powerless inside.

18:24.494 --> 18:29.325
- Well, if this thing
somehow possessed someone,

18:29.369 --> 18:30.935
we got to exorcise it.

18:30.979 --> 18:32.633
We have to save 'em.

18:32.676 --> 18:37.116
That's the code
the JSA lives by, right?

18:37.159 --> 18:41.816
That's the code you live by.

18:41.859 --> 18:45.820
- Yes, of course.

18:45.863 --> 18:48.692
You're right, Pat.

18:56.700 --> 18:59.181
There's always a way.

19:09.713 --> 19:12.412
[thunder crashing]

19:12.455 --> 19:15.415
[soft dramatic music]

19:15.458 --> 19:22.161
♪

19:28.254 --> 19:30.908
- 72 degrees?
Yeah, right.

19:30.952 --> 19:33.433
♪

19:33.476 --> 19:35.609
[knocking on door]

19:35.652 --> 19:42.964
♪

19:43.747 --> 19:45.619
[knocking on door]

19:51.364 --> 19:52.452
Cameron?
- Hey.

19:52.495 --> 19:55.368
- Hey, come in.
Hey.

19:55.411 --> 19:58.022
- I got caught in the storm.
I didn't know where else to go.

19:58.066 --> 20:01.504
- No, yeah, it's cool.
- Came out of nowhere.

20:01.548 --> 20:07.118
- Yeah, seems like a normal,
everyday storm to me.

20:09.469 --> 20:13.342
- Is Courtney here?

20:13.386 --> 20:16.084
- She's upstairs.

20:16.127 --> 20:18.739
- Where's your mom?

20:18.782 --> 20:22.090
[wind whooshing]

20:38.498 --> 20:42.415
[engine grinding]

20:42.458 --> 20:44.852
- Come on!

20:55.602 --> 20:58.213
- Hello, Barbara.

21:11.922 --> 21:14.360
We have a lot to catch up on,
don't we?

21:14.403 --> 21:16.362
[ice crackles]

21:27.764 --> 21:30.245
- Nice fire.

21:33.596 --> 21:38.645
- I told you, you can go up
and see Courtney if you want.

21:38.688 --> 21:41.038
- I will.

21:55.792 --> 21:57.359
[chuckles]

21:57.403 --> 22:00.144
Must be nice

22:00.188 --> 22:02.625
to be part of a family
like this.

22:02.669 --> 22:05.236
- Uh, yeah.

22:05.280 --> 22:07.369
[laughs]

22:07.413 --> 22:11.678
- You and your dad
are pretty close, huh?

22:11.721 --> 22:14.420
Yeah, I was close
with my dad, too.

22:17.597 --> 22:20.730
- You sure you're not cold?

22:20.774 --> 22:22.819
- Is it cold?

22:26.214 --> 22:29.478
You know, I lost my mother
when I was eight.

22:31.437 --> 22:35.092
How old are you?
- 15.

22:38.052 --> 22:43.057
- So you got seven more years
than I did.

22:43.100 --> 22:47.235
Oh, wait,
she's your stepmother, right?

22:47.278 --> 22:50.717
So I guess her loss
won't be that hard on you.

22:50.760 --> 22:52.327
I mean, it won't be as bad

22:52.371 --> 22:56.113
as when your real mother
abandoned you, will it?

22:59.116 --> 23:01.641
- Who told you that?

23:01.684 --> 23:03.991
- A friend.

23:04.034 --> 23:09.344
That same friend also told me
about my father,

23:09.388 --> 23:13.609
how you ran him over
and left him for dead.

23:13.653 --> 23:15.524
[tense music]

23:15.568 --> 23:17.613
- It was an accident.

23:17.657 --> 23:21.965
I didn't mean--I didn't mean
to kill him.

23:22.009 --> 23:23.967
- [chuckles]

23:24.011 --> 23:26.970
You didn't.

23:27.014 --> 23:29.930
He's still here.

23:29.973 --> 23:32.889
He's with Barbara right now.

23:32.933 --> 23:37.590
And I'm here with you.

23:37.633 --> 23:41.681
♪

23:41.724 --> 23:43.509
- [exhales]

23:53.693 --> 23:56.913
[wind whooshing]

23:58.741 --> 24:03.006
- You're dead, Jordan.
You're not here.

24:03.050 --> 24:05.182
This is Eclipso.

24:05.226 --> 24:08.490
- Eclipso?
No.

24:08.534 --> 24:13.016
No, this storm is my doing.
It's my rebirth.

24:13.060 --> 24:16.237
It was all gonna be
so wonderful, Barbara.

24:16.280 --> 24:18.021
- This isn't real.

24:18.065 --> 24:19.545
- I would have protected you
and Courtney

24:19.588 --> 24:21.938
from all
of this other nonsense.

24:21.982 --> 24:23.636
- It's not real.

24:23.679 --> 24:26.682
- But you betrayed me.

24:26.726 --> 24:29.903
You hurt me.

24:29.946 --> 24:32.645
So now it's time I hurt you.

24:32.688 --> 24:36.649
♪

24:36.692 --> 24:38.825
- Court?

24:38.868 --> 24:42.089
Courtney?
Dad?

24:42.132 --> 24:46.093
- No one is coming
to save you, Mike.

24:46.136 --> 24:47.877
[dog barks]

24:47.921 --> 24:51.490
[growling]

24:54.754 --> 24:58.932
[barking]

24:58.975 --> 24:59.976
[whines]

25:00.020 --> 25:02.805
- Buddy!
No!

25:02.849 --> 25:04.328
No.

25:08.202 --> 25:10.987
- Everyone in this house
is going to die.

25:13.903 --> 25:15.601
- [shouts]

25:17.951 --> 25:18.995
[yelps]

25:19.039 --> 25:26.089
♪

25:26.525 --> 25:28.396
- You could have helped me
save our country

25:28.439 --> 25:30.180
from itself, Barbara.

25:30.224 --> 25:34.315
Admit it.
A part of you wanted to.

25:37.231 --> 25:39.886
- Like I said before,
you're insane.

25:39.929 --> 25:42.584
- Insane?
No.

25:42.628 --> 25:44.673
No, I was in love, Barbara.

25:44.717 --> 25:47.633
For the first time since
my wife died, I was in love.

25:47.676 --> 25:51.201
- Barbara, he's not real.

25:51.245 --> 25:53.203
Your car, start it.

25:53.247 --> 25:55.292
- I tried, I tried.
It won't.

25:55.336 --> 25:56.859
- There's nothing wrong
with it.

25:56.903 --> 25:58.426
- There's no escaping me,
Barbara.

25:58.469 --> 25:59.732
- Damn it, Barbara.

25:59.775 --> 26:01.472
Ignore this nightmare
and start the bloody car.

26:01.516 --> 26:03.953
- I will haunt you
and your family forever.

26:03.997 --> 26:05.825
- Now!

26:05.868 --> 26:08.784
[engine turns over]

26:18.620 --> 26:20.056
Go home.

26:20.100 --> 26:25.714
I need...Emily?

26:25.758 --> 26:27.716
- Shade.

26:40.990 --> 26:43.950
[dramatic music]

26:43.993 --> 26:47.780
♪

26:47.823 --> 26:49.869
- [gagging]

26:49.912 --> 26:54.917
- You killed my dad,
so I get to kill your dad.

26:54.961 --> 26:57.920
I mean, that's fair, right?

26:57.964 --> 27:03.883
And you thought you were going
to be some kind of hero?

27:03.926 --> 27:06.059
But you're nothing.

27:06.102 --> 27:09.192
Unwanted by the JSA,

27:09.236 --> 27:15.155
like you were unwanted
by your own mother.

27:15.198 --> 27:17.374
- [grunting]

27:17.418 --> 27:22.728
♪

27:22.771 --> 27:25.208
- Mike?

27:25.252 --> 27:32.563
♪

27:33.129 --> 27:37.046
Mike, are you okay?

27:37.090 --> 27:39.919
- Court, look out!
- What is it?

27:39.962 --> 27:41.224
- Cameron's here,
and he's freaking out.

27:41.268 --> 27:45.751
- Mike, Mike!
No one is here.

27:45.794 --> 27:47.622
- Oh.
I just saw him.

27:47.666 --> 27:51.931
He had powers like his dad,
and he killed Buddy.

27:51.974 --> 27:54.629
- Oh.
[dog barks]

27:54.673 --> 27:57.937
- Hey, Buddy.
Hey. Hey.

27:57.980 --> 28:02.202
- Buddy's okay.
You're okay.

28:03.943 --> 28:06.772
Where's Pat?

28:06.815 --> 28:08.687
- I don't know.

28:15.955 --> 28:18.914
[tense music]

28:18.958 --> 28:25.747
♪

28:34.060 --> 28:36.671
[thunder crashes]

29:11.184 --> 29:18.495
♪

29:45.044 --> 29:51.833
♪

29:58.013 --> 30:00.929
- Pat! Pat!

30:00.973 --> 30:04.106
Pat! Pat!

30:04.150 --> 30:07.109
[tense music]

30:07.153 --> 30:14.116
♪

30:14.160 --> 30:15.944
[elevator dings]

30:24.997 --> 30:26.999
- What are you guys doing
down here?

30:27.042 --> 30:29.610
- There were four of us sitting
around the table tonight,

30:29.653 --> 30:32.613
but we needed an odd number,
in case of a tie.

30:34.223 --> 30:35.834
- Tie for what?

30:35.877 --> 30:38.924
- Green Lantern and The Spectre
couldn't stop it.

30:38.967 --> 30:43.885
Dr. Fate, The Hawks--
Eclipso beat them all,

30:43.929 --> 30:47.933
and he vowed
to kill our families too.

30:47.976 --> 30:49.586
We're out of time.

30:49.630 --> 30:50.936
- So we're voting.

30:50.979 --> 30:52.459
It comes down to it,
we got to do what

30:52.502 --> 30:54.809
The Shade said
and take out the host.

30:58.944 --> 31:02.425
- Talking about killing a man?

31:02.469 --> 31:04.775
If you do that, I mean,

31:04.819 --> 31:07.256
it goes against everything
that we stand for.

31:07.300 --> 31:08.823
- We?

31:08.867 --> 31:12.348
Last time I checked,
you were the mechanic.

31:12.392 --> 31:14.220
We're the ones that are putting
our lives on the line and have

31:14.263 --> 31:16.613
to make decisions like this
that we don't want to make.

31:16.657 --> 31:19.094
You ain't a member
of this team, Stripesy.

31:19.138 --> 31:21.575
You're Sly's driver,
so stay in your lane.

31:21.618 --> 31:24.186
- That's enough, Ted.
- Sorry.

31:24.230 --> 31:25.753
I just call them
like I see them.

31:25.796 --> 31:28.060
- Nobody wants to do this,

31:28.103 --> 31:29.975
but we might have to

31:30.018 --> 31:31.715
for Rebecca.

31:31.759 --> 31:35.458
- We came together
to find justice, not vengeance.

31:35.502 --> 31:38.940
Didn't we, Rex?
Ted?

31:38.984 --> 31:41.682
Sylvester, we're talking about
victimizing a victim here.

31:41.725 --> 31:45.686
- I got a son,
so I'm gonna do what I gotta.

31:45.729 --> 31:49.429
Let's vote.
I'm a yes.

31:51.126 --> 31:53.955
- I'm obviously a no.

31:53.999 --> 31:56.175
- I don't want to hurt anybody.

31:56.218 --> 32:00.614
But if there's no other choice,
if it comes down to it...

32:02.137 --> 32:07.099
I'm gonna do what we have to
to protect our families.

32:07.142 --> 32:09.884
Yes.

32:09.928 --> 32:11.538
- Pat?
- He shouldn't get a vote.

32:11.581 --> 32:14.497
- He does.
Pat?

32:14.541 --> 32:16.195
- I vote no.

32:16.238 --> 32:18.632
It's like Starman says.
There's always a way.

32:18.675 --> 32:20.503
- That's two to two.

32:20.547 --> 32:23.724
- So it's down to Sylvester,
right?

32:23.767 --> 32:26.248
Then it's decided.

32:26.292 --> 32:29.991
It's two for
but three against.

32:30.035 --> 32:34.343
- My vote's a yes.

32:34.387 --> 32:36.041
- What?

32:39.870 --> 32:42.525
- Eclipso threatened
my family, too.

32:42.569 --> 32:44.658
I'll do whatever it takes
to protect them.

32:44.701 --> 32:46.616
- I won't take part in this.

32:46.660 --> 32:49.489
- You won't have to, Jay.

32:49.532 --> 32:54.015
Get the car ready.

32:54.059 --> 32:57.410
- No.

32:57.453 --> 33:01.327
I voted no.

33:01.370 --> 33:04.721
- Right now.

33:04.765 --> 33:11.728
♪

33:11.772 --> 33:14.035
- It'll never come off.

33:17.299 --> 33:21.390
And your children's blood
will be on your hands next.

33:21.434 --> 33:24.611
[dramatic music]

33:24.654 --> 33:31.618
♪

33:31.661 --> 33:35.578
You had a choice,
and you made it.

33:35.622 --> 33:40.627
♪

33:40.670 --> 33:42.890
You damned yourselves.

33:48.113 --> 33:49.505
- Pat?

33:49.549 --> 33:52.508
[soft music]

33:52.552 --> 33:56.208
♪

33:56.251 --> 33:58.645
You okay?

33:58.688 --> 34:06.000
♪

34:13.660 --> 34:17.185
[soft dramatic music]

34:17.229 --> 34:21.233
- No one's gonna hurt you.

34:21.276 --> 34:25.367
No one.
Hey.

34:25.411 --> 34:27.587
All right?

34:27.630 --> 34:34.942
♪

34:41.514 --> 34:44.169
- You sure you're okay?

34:44.212 --> 34:46.562
- I am, thanks to you.

34:48.999 --> 34:52.568
- What did you see?

34:52.612 --> 34:54.788
- A lot.

34:58.008 --> 35:00.924
Bruce Gordon.
- What?

35:00.968 --> 35:02.926
Why?

35:05.668 --> 35:08.671
What haven't you told me, Pat?

35:08.715 --> 35:12.153
♪

35:12.197 --> 35:18.464
- I've never told you how
the JSA really stopped Eclipso.

35:18.507 --> 35:25.819
♪

35:39.311 --> 35:41.617
[exhaling]

35:47.536 --> 35:50.278
Oh, come on.
Come on.

36:02.856 --> 36:05.250
[staff warbles, powers down]

36:08.557 --> 36:11.256
What happened?

36:11.299 --> 36:13.823
- You were right.

36:13.867 --> 36:17.175
JSA should never take a life.

36:23.964 --> 36:25.879
But it's too late.

36:25.922 --> 36:31.928
♪

36:31.972 --> 36:35.236
- [screaming]

36:38.631 --> 36:40.633
- We need to get this
to storage.

36:40.676 --> 36:42.374
- Sylvester--
- Drive.

36:42.417 --> 36:44.811
- Wait a minute.
- Damn it, drive, Pat.

36:44.854 --> 36:47.422
It's over.

36:47.466 --> 36:49.990
It's all over.

36:58.868 --> 37:00.696
[engine turns over]

37:00.740 --> 37:03.046
- There was no last meeting.

37:03.090 --> 37:07.268
There was no decision
to break up.

37:07.312 --> 37:10.793
Everyone just drifted away
after that.

37:15.058 --> 37:16.799
[latches click]

37:16.843 --> 37:19.149
I kept coming around, though,

37:19.193 --> 37:23.763
hoping to see if any of them
showed up around the table.

37:23.806 --> 37:26.940
Nobody did.

37:26.983 --> 37:30.813
Not until the ISA reformed,
but...

37:30.857 --> 37:33.425
you know,
that was a lot of years later.

37:33.468 --> 37:36.645
And even when the JSA
got back together,

37:36.689 --> 37:39.953
well, they were never the same.

37:39.996 --> 37:43.522
They were broken.

37:43.565 --> 37:47.352
And that's why the ISA won
in the end.

37:47.395 --> 37:51.660
Killing Bruce Gordon--

37:51.704 --> 37:54.881
when the JSA did that...

37:57.492 --> 38:00.887
It wound up killing them.

38:06.588 --> 38:09.504
- We promised.

38:09.548 --> 38:10.984
No more secrets.

38:11.027 --> 38:12.464
- I know, Court.
- You've been--

38:12.507 --> 38:14.727
you've been lying to me
for weeks, Pat,

38:14.770 --> 38:17.773
lying while my friends
were being hurt

38:17.817 --> 38:21.386
and destroyed by Eclipso.

38:28.175 --> 38:32.397
What's my mom going to say?

38:32.440 --> 38:35.400
[soft music]

38:35.443 --> 38:37.402
♪

38:37.445 --> 38:39.360
- She knows.

38:39.404 --> 38:42.363
[Jordan Critz's
"No Matter What"]

38:42.407 --> 38:46.280
♪

38:46.324 --> 38:49.718
- ♪ It cut you wide open

38:49.762 --> 38:54.027
♪ It doesn't take much
for a human to break ♪

38:54.070 --> 38:57.378
♪ A world of emotions

38:57.422 --> 38:59.554
♪ And there's only so much

38:59.598 --> 39:03.297
- Is everyone okay in here?
- Hey, Barb, you all right?

39:05.430 --> 39:07.562
- Why did you lie to me?

39:07.606 --> 39:11.174
[indistinct conversation]

39:11.218 --> 39:14.830
[indistinct yelling]

39:14.874 --> 39:19.879
♪

39:32.500 --> 39:33.936
[child cackling]

39:55.001 --> 39:56.394
- Greg, move your head.
